[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " At that time,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Naomi, her mother-in-law, said to her, “My daughter, I must find a home for you so you will be secure."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now Boaz, with whose female servants you worked, is our close relative."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Look, tonight he is winnowing barley at the threshing floor."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So bathe yourself,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " rub on some perfumed oil,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and get dressed up."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then go down"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to the threshing floor. But don’t let the man know you’re there until he finishes his meal."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When he gets ready to go to sleep,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " take careful notice of the place where he lies down. Then go, uncover his legs,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and lie down"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " beside him."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He will tell"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " you what you should do.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Ruth replied to Naomi,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “I will do everything you have told"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " me"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to do.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So she went down to the threshing floor and did everything her mother-in-law had instructed her to do."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When Boaz had finished his meal and was feeling satisfied, he lay down to sleep at the far end of the grain heap."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Ruth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " crept up quietly,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " uncovered his legs,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and lay down beside him."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " In the middle of the night he was startled"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and turned over."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " he saw a woman"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " lying beside him!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He said, “Who are you?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " She replied, “I am Ruth, your servant."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Marry your servant,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for you are a guardian of the family interests.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He said, “May you be rewarded"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " by the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", my dear!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " This act of devotion"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is greater than what you did before."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For you have not sought to marry"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " one of the young men, whether rich or poor."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now, my dear, don’t worry!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I intend to do for you everything you propose,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for everyone in the village"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " knows that you are a worthy woman."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now yes, it is true that"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I am a guardian,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but there is another guardian who is a closer relative than I am. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Remain here tonight. Then in the morning, if he agrees to marry you,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " fine,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " let him do so."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But if he does not want to do so, I promise, as surely as the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " lives, to marry you."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Sleep here until morning.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So she slept beside him"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " until morning. She woke up while it was still dark."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Boaz thought,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “No one must know that a woman visited the threshing floor.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then he said, “Hold out the shawl"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " you are wearing"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and grip it tightly.” As she held it tightly, he measured out about sixty pounds"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of barley into the shawl and put it on her shoulders. Then he"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " went into town, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and she returned to her mother-in-law."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "When Ruth returned to her mother-in-law, Naomi"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " asked,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “How did things turn out for you,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " my daughter?” Ruth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " told her about all the man had done for her."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " She said, “He gave me these sixty pounds of barley, for he said to me,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " ‘Do not go to your mother-in-law empty-handed.’”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Naomi"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said, “Stay put,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " my daughter, until you know how the matter turns out. For the man will not rest until he has taken care of the matter today.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]